commit.message:
Automatically disable pytest-cov report when using e3 pytest plugin

When using e3 pytest plugin, some coverage options are set. For
instance we ignore some lines in the code source, or omit some files.
The pytest-cov report is not accurate and is automatically disabled
in that case.
Fix release dates

Create a pytest plugin to reuse fixtures in other projects

Remove deprecated requirements traceability which is not maintained.
Create e3.pytest to reuse part of the code in conftest.py in other
projects.
Document the new plugin.

commit.message:
Fix typing information for Checkout events

The possible values in the dictionary are not necessarily strings:
the release_branching_info field is actually a dict.

Add ability to perform actions before processing of platform arguments

Add ability to call a callback before processing --build,--host and
--target in e3.main.Main.parse_args. This allows for example to adjust
Env before processing the platform related arguments (such as changing
the default).

Update e3-pypi-closure to generate more precise version

Ensure that patch version generated when using
'update_wheel_version_file' option in a config file contains the
time at which the package is generated. This ensures that several
versions of the same package can be generated during a given day

commit.message: Type e3.anod.sandbox.scripts module

Do not assume Git default branch is called "master"

Running git init won't always create a "master" branch. More and
more configurations creates a branch named "main", and the name of the
initial branch can be changed using:
    [init]
        defaultBranch = nameofbranch

To get the first branch created by git init, run:

     git branch --show-current

Do not use assert to skip a test but rely on skipif()

Otherwise, we get an error when running the testsuite.

Also adjust pytest.mark.skipif to enable test_rlimit_foreground_option
on macOS.

Bump mypy to 1.8.0 in pyproject.toml

For it/org/software-supply-chain/production-pipeline/issues#44
